      • find

        public BinaryTreeNode<dataType> find​(dataType d,
                                     BinaryTreeNode<dataType> node)
        This method searches the BST, it uses the compareTo method to inspect nodes and search through the tree. If the compareTo method returns something less 0 than it will recursivly run the find function on the left Node, and visa versa for something greater than 0
        Parameters:
        d - this is an argument for the object which will be searched for in the tree.
        node - this is the current node which is being comparedTo the argument @param d
        Returns:
        this will return the Binary Tree Node which is equal to the object being searched for.

      • delete

        public BinaryTreeNode<dataType> delete​(dataType d,
                                       BinaryTreeNode<dataType> node)
        Remvoes a node from the BST by recursivly calling the delete function. This will use the compareTo method to test if the node which will be deleted is the current node
        Parameters:
        d - the node which is going to be deleted
        node - the current node that is selected in the BST
        Returns:
        returns a Binary Tree Node. This will be the root of the current node, which will remove the current node. or a null value if there is @param node is null

      • findMin

        public BinaryTreeNode<dataType> findMin​(BinaryTreeNode<dataType> node)
        Finds the minimum value of the BST from a node by traversing the left half of the tree from that node.
        Parameters:
        node - the starting node in the tree (to find the absolute min one should set this to the root)
        Returns:
